<sect1>Compilation and installation
<p>

In order to compile and install TuxCards on your system, type the following in
the base directory of the TuxCards distribution:

<tscreen><verb>
% ./configure
% make
% make install
</verb></tscreen>

<p>
Since TuxCards uses <verb>autoconf</verb> you should have not trouble
compiling it.
Should you run into problems please report them to the the author at 
<htmlurl url="mailto:alex.theel@gmx.net" name = "Alexander Theel">


